==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Souse
<hw>Souse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>sausse</ets>.
See <er>Sauce</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also <asp>souce</asp>,
<asp>sowce</asp>, and <asp>sowse</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pickle
made with salt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something kept or steeped in pickle; esp., the
pickled ears, feet, etc., of swine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And he that can rear up a pig in his house,⟦br⟧
Hath cheaper his bacon, and sweeter his <qex>souse</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tusser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The ear; especially, a hog's ear.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The act of sousing; a plunging into water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souse</ent>⟦br⟧

