==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Souse
<hw>Souse</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Soused</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sousing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>saucer</ets> to wet
with sauce. See <er>Souse</er> pickle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To steep
in pickle; to pickle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>soused</xex> gurnet.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To plunge or immerse in water or any
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>soused</qex> me over head and ears in water.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To drench, as by an immersion; to wet
throughly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Although I be well <qex>soused</qex> in this shower.</q>
<rj><qau>Gascoigne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Souse
<hw>Souse</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Probably fr. OF. <ets>sors</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>sordre</ets> to rise, and first used of an upward swood,
then of a swoop in general, but also confused with <er>Souse</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> See <er>Source</er>.]</ety> <def>To swoop or plunge, as
a bird upon its prey; to fall suddenly; to rush with speed; to make a
sudden attack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For then I viewed his plunge and <qex>souse</qex>⟦br⟧
Into the foamy main.</q> <rj><qau>Marston.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jove's bird will <qex>souse</qex> upon the timorous hare.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Dryden. Jr.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Souse
<hw>Souse</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To pounce upon.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[The gallant monarch] like eagle o'er his serie towers,⟦br⟧
To <qex>souse</qex> annoyance that comes near his nest.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 7 ====
HEADWORD: Souse
<hw>Souse</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of sousing, or
swooping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As a falcon fair⟦br⟧
